From c244021f145c298911d9f9f57757680ed58afcf9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 21:35:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add 2x/4x oversampling around the waveshaper (milestone 7)

The waveshaper generates harmonics above Nyquist that fold back as inharmonic
aliasing, most audible on FOLD and high drive. This wraps only the nonlinearity
(the sole aliasing source) in a polyphase FIR oversampler:

- Windowed-sinc (Blackman) 32-tap prototype, split into two 16-tap polyphase
  components for interpolation and decimation.
- A single 2x stage; two cascade for 4x. All state stack-allocated, no heap.
- New EnumParam (Off/2x/4x, default 2x) and an Oversample control in OUTPUT.

Pre/post EQ stay at base rate since they are linear and do not alias.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
